preference.name: CATANALYSIS_item_type
preference.preference_description: Define a list of item types to use when saving a part, product, drawing, process, analysis or design table, by setting the following variables within Teamcenter Preferences. The default value of the item type is determined as follows: If the item type is defined in the CATPART_item_type, CATPRODUCT_item_type, etc. preference, then the item type used is the first listed in the preference list. The Save Manager only displays the available (defined) item types. If the item type preference is not defined, a list of all item types available in Teamcenter displays, and the default item type is defined by the CATIA_item_type Teamcenter Preference. If this type is not available then the first item type in Teamcenter list is the default item type. When Create New is applied from the Save Manager, the displayed item type is the existing item type. If this type is not available, then default values are used.

preference.name: CATIA_PSE_alternate_preferred_bv
preference.preference_description:
If the item revision of a part features several BOM View Revisions and you create an occurrence of it within an assembly, the native behavior of Teamcenter is to use the first BOM View Revision type found. To define a specific list of BOM View Types used in Teamcenter (for leaf node Parts only), create a new variable within CATIA_PSE_alternate_preferred_bv in Teamcenter Preferences. The first type listed becomes the most preferred one. For example:
CATIA_PSE_alternate_preferred_bv= newView1 newView2 newView3
A blank line marks the end of the list. The list is sorted in order of preference, i.e., the first type displayed in the list is the most preferred one. If the CATIA_PSE_alternate_preferred_bv variable is not defined, Teamcenter uses the first BOM View Revision type found.

preference.name: CATIA_component_dataset_types

For example: CATIA_component_dataset_types = myDatasetType1 myDatasetType2 This list can be slightly different from what is used by the Integration. For each dataset type defined in the list, define the Named Reference to load by defining a new variable built within the dataset type name defined in the CATIA_component_dataset_typesvariable. preference.name: CATIA_priority_dst_type_list_for_parameters
preference.preference_description: List of dataset types, in order of priority, used to determine the dataset type(s) of the parameter data under an Item Revision. The last type has the least priority. This preference will be applied systematically, whether or not there are datasets under Item Revision, on the list of datasets type present under Item Revision being processed, completed by the type of dataset selected by the current process executed on the Item Revision or on the document in CATIA. Example for the Load: the list of dataset types will come from the combination of the types of dataset present under the Item Revison and the type of dataset selected by the load process (Case of seed documents) For Save (and similar) processes, the list of dataset type present under Item Revision will be determined after the creation of all datasets present under this Item Revision. This in order to manage the cases of linked documents. The types of dataset that are not present in the preference, will not own the parameter data Default empty value is applied when the preference does not exist, if it is empty or incorrectly filled. There is no order of priority in this case. The parameter data present under the Item Revision belongs to all the types of dataset present under the Item Revision, as well as to the type of the dataset used by the current process executed on the Item Revision or on the document in CATIA. The types of dataset selected must be part of this type list: CATIA_CATPart_dataset_type, CATIA_CATProduct_dataset_type, CATIA_CATDrawing_dataset_type, CATIA_CATProcess_dataset_type, CATIA_CATAnalysis_dataset_type, CATIA_component_dataset_types

The default value is true. If the value of this property is set to false, visualization data files will be stored in the TS Proxy User default volume. The TS Proxy User MUST be granted access to all volumes where source dataset data files are stored unless the value of this property is false. This property must be specified such that it applies to all Services.

preference.name: CATIA_query_for_item_rev_browser
preference.preference_description: Defines the default query used by item revisions browser.

preference.name: CATIA_read_publication_timestamps
preference.preference_description: Set the Read Publication Timestamps variable to true to read the timestamps of all publications. Set this variable to false to read the timestamps of parts instead of publications.

preference.name: CATIA_reference_prefix
preference.preference_description: Defines the prefix used during the Export as reference process for part numbers and file names of reference documents

preference.name: CATIA_reference_prefix_partnumber
preference.preference_description: Prefix used for part numbers for reference documents.

preference.name: CATIA_reference_product_partnumber
preference.preference_description: Define the default names of the product to create in CATIA, to load an assembly as a reference

preference.name: CATIA_refresh_bom_window_on_load
preference.preference_description: Defines the BOM window behavior during the load process. - Refresh the BOM window during the load process (YES) - Do not refresh the BOM window during the load process (NO) - Provide prompt to refresh the BOM window during the load process (WARNING)

preference.name: CATIA_refresh_bom_window_on_load_2
preference.preference_description: Defines the BOM window behavior during the load process. Possible values: YES = Refresh the BOM window during the load process NO = Do not refresh the BOM window during the load process WARNING = Provide prompt to refresh the BOM window during the load process

preference.name: CATIA_refresh_bom_window_on_save
preference.preference_description: Defines which BOM window should be refreshed at the end of a Save process. Possible values: - ACTIVE: Refresh the active BOM window - OF_TOP_LEVEL: Refresh the BOM window corresponding to the saved assembly - IF_SAVE_PROD: Refresh the BOM window corresponding to the saved assembly only when products are saved - NONE: No refresh is done at the end of a save process

preference.name: CATIA_refresh_catalog_comp_in_browser
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether referenced documents selected in the Catalog Browser should be refreshed. Values: True: Refresh each referenced document selected in the Catalog Browser. False: Do not refresh referenced documents in the Catalog Browser.

preference.name: CATIA_refresh_teamcenter_on_load
preference.preference_description: Refresh Teamcenter or not during Load process

preference.name: CATIA_rename_analysis_filename
preference.preference_description: When an item is saved, you can also rename the filename of the CATPart, CATProduct, CATProcess or CATAnalysis documents independently by modifying the three characters within those variables. Each of the three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. For example: - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 000.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_catalog_comp_filename
preference.preference_description: Renames the filename of a document referenced in the catalog independently of other documents when an item is saved. Three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 000.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_catalog_filename
preference.preference_description: Renames the catalog filename independently of other documents when an item is saved. Three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 000.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_designtable_filename
preference.preference_description: When an item is saved, you can also rename the filename of the CATPart, CATProduct, CATProcess or CATAnalysis documents independently by modifying the three characters within those variables. Each of the three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. For example: - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 101.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_drawing_dataset_in_post_action
preference.preference_description: Set to true to rename Drawing datasets during the Save As/Revise Post Action, set to false to not rename.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_foreignfile_filename
preference.preference_description: Specifies the actions permitted on foreign files during a save process. Foreign files can be independently renamed during a save process depending on the three character value of this preference; each character represents the setting for a specific save operation. For example: 0 = renaming the foreign file is not permitted during this operation (see below) 1 = renaming the foreign file is permitted during this operation (see below) The value of the first character applies to the Save As operation. The value of the second character applies to the Save Existing operation. The value of the third character applies to the Save New Revision operation. The default value is 111, indicating that foreign files may be independently renamed during the Save As, Save Existing and Save New Revision operations

preference.name: CATIA_rename_jt_from_nx
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_rename_jt_from_nx variable to true to be able to load JT datasets created with NX software in CATIA V5.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_part_filename
preference.preference_description: Renames the CATPart filename independently of other documents when an item is saved. Three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 111.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_partnumber_during_lfc
preference.preference_description: Use the file name prefix for the part number prefix during the Load For Compare process (True) Do not use the file name prefix for the part number prefix prefix during the Load For Compare process (False)

preference.name: CATIA_rename_process_filename
preference.preference_description: When an item is saved, you can also rename the filename of the CATPart, CATProduct, CATProcess or CATAnalysis documents independently by modifying the three characters within those variables. Each of the three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. For example: - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 000.

preference.name: CATIA_rename_product_filename
preference.preference_description: When an item is saved, you can also rename the filename of the CATPart, CATProduct, CATProcess or CATAnalysis documents independently by modifying the three characters within those variables. Each of the three characters represent an action to be carried out on the document to save. For example: - 0 = no modification - 1 = modification The first character of the variable applies to the SAVE AS function. The second character of the variable applies to the SAVE EXISTING function. The third character of the variable applies to the SAVE NEW REVISION function. The default values are 111.

preference.name: CATIA_replace_by_revision_with_latest
preference.preference_description: Use the latest revision during the Replace by revision process (True) Do not use the latest revision during the Replace by revision process (False)

preference.name: CATIA_replace_special_character
preference.preference_description: Customize the character used to replace the special characters displayed the file name, by setting the following variable within Teamcenter Preferences.

preference.name: CATIA_reposition_rigidAssy
preference.preference_description: Repositions occurrences in rigid assembly during load process

preference.name: CATIA_saveActiveShapeName
preference.preference_description: Use the following variable within Teamcenter Preferences to customize the toggle buttons of the Save Manager toolbar. Customize the Save Active Shapes button.

preference.name: CATIA_save_all_drawings_in_session
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether commands SAVE/SAVE AS/SAVE SELECTED manage drawings during the save of CATPart or CATProduct. Not case sensitive. Possible values: - Yes: Run the Save command managing Drawings when the active document in CATIA are a CATPart or a CATProduct - No: Run the Save command not managing Drawings when the active document in CATIA are a CATPart or a CATProduct. - Question: Display a prompt when the active document in CATIA are a CATPart or a CATProduct, asking to perform a Save managing Drawings. "Do you want to save Drawings in session?"

preference.name: CATIA_save_analysis_option
preference.preference_description: Defines whether the CATAnalysisComputations files or the CATAnalysisResults files are saved in the Database during the save process. (Simple value, case insensitive) both = Save both CATAnalysisComputations and CATAnalysisResults files. analysisCompute = Only Save CATAnalysisComputations file. analysisResult = Only Save CATAnalysisResults file. none = Do not Save CATAnalysisComputations files nor CATAnalysisResults files.

preference.name: CATIA_save_existing_item_without_dataset
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_save_existing_item_without_dataset preference to false to prevent items in an assembly, that do not have a related CATIA V5 dataset in Teamcenter, from being saved from CATIA to Teamcenter.

preference.name: CATIA_save_mass_properties
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_save_mass_properties variable to true to read Mass Properties during the Save to Teamcenter process. Set this variable to false to prevent Mass Properties from being read during the Save to Teamcenter process.

preference.name: CATIA_save_material
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_save_material variable to true to read Material during the Save to Teamcenter process. Set this variable to false to prevent Material from being read during the Save to Teamcenter process.

preference.name: CATIA_save_only_pointed_publications
preference.preference_description: Controls the conditions in which Publications are saved. If catia_manage_publications_on_save = true and : - CATIA_save_only_pointed_publications = true then only CATIA publications identified as link are saved in Teamcenter. - CATIA_save_only_pointed_publications = false then all CATIA publications are saved in Teamcenter.

preference.name: CATIA_save_shapes_under_released_cad_element
preference.preference_description: Allow or not saving of shapes representations appearing as modified or new in CATIA under a release item revision

preference.name: CATIA_save_supplier_info
preference.preference_description: Set the Save Supplier Properties variable to true to save supplier properties. Set this variable to false to prevent supplier properties from being saved

preference.name: CATIA_saved_modified_file_option
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_saved_modified_file_option preference to true to only save modified files or to false to save both modified and unmodified files. This preference has an interaction on the Force Save Unmodified files button in the Save Manager and is also taken into account during batch processes.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_actions_list
preference.preference_description: List of available actions in the Action section. Possible values: main_body_geo: corresponds to "Compute geometry for main body only" option project: corresponds to "Project to assign" option workflow: corresponds to "Workflow to apply" option

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_apply_existing_documents_without_dataset_filter
preference.preference_description: Provide the Ability to manage an additional Warning Filter dedicated to "Hide existing documents without dataset" warning message when there is no dataset associated to the item Revision of the document. Additional filter is automatically applied when the save manager is launched if the preference is set to true (and if CATIA_save_existing_item_without_dataset is set to false).

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_auto_assign_item_rev_ids
preference.preference_description: true = Manage auto-assign IDs during a Save selection in the Save Manager false = Do not manage auto-assign IDs during a Save selection in the Save Manager

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_auto_ids_option
preference.preference_description: True : Auto ids check box is toggled on False : Auto ids check box is toggled off By default the value is set to true.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_auto_name_option
preference.preference_description: Set to true to toggle on Auto Name check box , set to false to toggle off.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_catalog_comp_save_modes
preference.preference_description: List of keywords defining the available save modes for documents referenced in a catalog. Only save modes listed in this preference can be applied to documents referenced in a catalog. Possible values : CREATE = Create New and Save As New save modes are available COPY = Save As Copy save mode is available REVISE = New Revision save mode is available USE EXISTING ITEM = Use Existing Item save mode is available. Permits a new dataset to be created under and existing item. USE EXISTING DATASET = Use Existing Dataset save mode is available (to update a dataset under an existing item) EXISTING = Existing save mode is available

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_default_folder
preference.preference_description: Defines the Teamcenter folder displayed in the Save Manager, by default. Possible values: none, folder name (master value)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_display_item_attr_on_saveas
preference.preference_description: Display only the item revision's object_name and object_desc attributes in the Save Manager during the Save As mode (false). Display both the object_name and object_desc attributes of item and item revision in the Save Manager during the Save As mode (true).

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_display_itemtab
preference.preference_description: true : Manage Item tab in SaveManager during a multiselection false : Do not manage Item tab in SaveManager during a multiselection

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_dynamiccrosshighlight_available
preference.preference_description: Enable the Dynamic Cross Highlight in the save process. Possible values: - TRUE = "Dynamic Cross Highlight" option is available - FALSE = The CATIA session is locked during the save process and the dynamic cross highlight is not supported.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_dynamiccrosshighlight_option
preference.preference_description: Toggle on/off the Dynamic Cross Highlight button in the Save Manager panel. Possible values: - TRUE = "Dynamic Cross Highlight" option is ON. - FALSE = "Dynamic Cross Highlight" option is OFF.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_hideshow_option
preference.preference_description: Manage Hide/Show assembly attributes outside the scene during the save process (True) Do Not manage Hide/Show assembly attributes outside the scene during the save process (False)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_hideshow_option_on_import
preference.preference_description: Manage Hide/Show assembly attributes outside the scene during the import process (True) Do Not manage Hide/Show assembly attributes outside the scene during the import process (False)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_itemtab_actions_list
preference.preference_description: List of available actions to display in the Actions section within the Item tab during a multi-selection. The value(s) of this preference must also be listed in the CATIA_savemanager_actions_list preference to be taken into account. Possible values: main_body_geo : corresponds to "Compute geometry for main body only" option project : corresponds to "Project to assign" option workflow : corresponds to "Workflow to apply" option

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_itemtab_sections
preference.preference_description: List of sections to display in the Item tab during a multi-selection. Sections are defined by the keywords : itemrev, relation, actions

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_manage_object_name_on_duplicate
preference.preference_description: Indicates if prefix, suffix, and substitute characters of duplicate panel are applied on the item/itemrev's object_name during the duplicate process. Possible values (not case sensitive) are : - true: the object_name and the item ID properties are managed - false: only the item ID property is managed (default behavior)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ds_object_desc
preference.preference_description: Map object_desc attribute diplayed in Dataset section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ds_object_name
preference.preference_description: Map object_name attribute diplayed in Dataset section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ds_object_type
preference.preference_description: Map object_type attribute diplayed in Dataset section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ds_pubr_object_id
preference.preference_description: Map pubr_object_id attribute diplayed in Dataset section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ds_rev
preference.preference_description: Map rev attribute diplayed in Dataset section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ir_item_id
preference.preference_description: Map item_id attribute diplayed in Item Revision section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ir_item_revision_id
preference.preference_description: Map item_revision attribute diplayed in Item Revision section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ir_object_desc
preference.preference_description: Map object_desc attribute diplayed in Item Revision section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ir_object_name
preference.preference_description: Map object_name attribute diplayed in Item Revision section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_map_ir_object_type
preference.preference_description: Map object_type attribute diplayed in Item Revision section of Save Manager with any of CATIA property

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_multisel_actions_list
preference.preference_description: List of available actions to display in the Actions section within the Document tab during a multi-selection. The value(s) of this preference must also be listed in the CATIA_savemanager_actions_list preference to be taken into account. Possible values: main_body_geo : corresponds to "Compute geometry for main body only" option project : corresponds to "Project to assign" option workflow : corresponds to "Workflow to apply" option

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_multisel_sections
preference.preference_description: List of sections to display in the Document tab during a multi-selection. Sections are defined by the keywords: itemrev, dataset, relations, actions

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_process_template_filter
preference.preference_description: Retrieve all process templates (ALL) or retrieve only assigned templates (ASSIGNED)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_process_template_under_construction
preference.preference_description: Retrieve all process templates (true), or retrieve all except "under construction" Templates (false)

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_relation_types_list
preference.preference_description: List of real names to display in the Save Manager of the possible relation types between the item revision and primary dataset

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_show_dynamic_cross_highlight_warning
preference.preference_description: When set to false: the dynamic cross highlight warning is no longer displayed. If "Do not show this message anymore" option is activated then this preference is set to false.

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_unmodifiable_assigned_attr_list
preference.preference_description: This preference defines an attribute list. These attributes will not be modified once they are assigned in the SaveManager. The attribute list must adhere to the naming format "keyword.attributename". List of keywords: - For item's attribute = Item. - For item revision's attribute = ItemRev. - For item master form's attribute = ItemMaster. - For item revision master form's attribute = ItemRevMaster. - For dataset's attribute = Dst. The attributename should be the attribute real name. For example: Item.item_id; ItemRev.item_revision_id

preference.name: CATIA_savemanager_unmodifiable_attr_list
preference.preference_description: This preference defines an attribute list. These attributes will not be modified in the SaveManager. The attribute list must adhere to the naming format "keyword.attributename". List of keywords: - For item's attribute = Item. - For item revision's attribute = ItemRev. - For item master form's attribute = ItemMaster. - For item revision master form's attribute = ItemRevMaster. - For dataset's attribute = Dst. The attributename should be the attribute real name. For example: Item.item_id; ItemRev.item_revision_id; Dst.pubr_object_id; Dst.object_name

preference.name: CATIA_search_external_ref_links_on_save
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_search_external_ref_links_on_save variable to true to search MML Links outside the assembly (ref-ref relationships) during the Save process to save them along with the assembly. Set this variable to false to prevent searching for ref-ref relationships.

preference.name: CATIA_search_flattening_links_on_save
preference.preference_description: When set to true, the Flattening links are managed by the integration during the save processes. When the link is built on a CATProduct not registered in the assembly, then the linked CATProduct is also saved in TcIC, if this one is accessible under the local disk.

preference.name: CATIA_search_mmlassy_links_on_save
preference.preference_description: Set to true to search MMLAssy Links between two parts in a same assembly (ref-inst relationships) and to expose links in Teamcenter during the Save process. Set to false, to prevent searching for ref-inst relationships.

preference.name: CATIA_secondary_link_type
preference.preference_description: Link type between item revision / CATProduct dataset and SecondaryPart datasets

preference.name: CATIA_secondary_model_dataset_type
preference.preference_description: Dataset type of model V4 SecondaryPart

preference.name: CATIA_secondary_part_dataset_type
preference.preference_description: Dataset type of SecondaryPart leaves of assembly

preference.name: CATIA_secondary_product_dataset_type
preference.preference_description: Dataset type of SecondaryPart nodes of assembly

preference.name: CATIA_seed_analysis_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document analysis

preference.name: CATIA_seed_catshape_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document catshape

preference.name: CATIA_seed_drawing_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document drawing

preference.name: CATIA_seed_part_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document part

preference.name: CATIA_seed_process_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document process

preference.name: CATIA_seed_product_id
preference.preference_description: Define the ID of an item for a seed document product

preference.name: CATIA_seedpanel_use_for_all
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the "Use this dataset for all" option in the Seed Panel is automatically selected (toggled on). Values: True: this option is selected in the Seed Panel False: this option is unselected in the Seed Panel

preference.name: CATIA_set_readonly_properties_on_create
preference.preference_description: Creates through mapping a new property, during Save/Load process, with ReadOnly mode. Example of possible values: - QC_MODEL_ASSESSMENT - QC_TOTAL_WEIGHT_SUM - QC_CHECKING_TOOL - QC_CHECKING_DATE - QC_CHECKING_TIME - QC_CHECKING_TIMEZONE - QC_PROFILE_NAME - QC_MODEL_CAD_VERSION - QC_RETURN_CODE

preference.name: CATIA_shapeProperties_form
preference.preference_description: form type to use to contain active shapes representations names

preference.name: CATIA_shapeProperties_link_type
preference.preference_description: GRM link type between item revision/bom line and shape actives form

preference.name: CATIA_show_create_catdrawing_menu
preference.preference_description: Add the "Create CATDrawing dataset for selection" menu in the Teamcenter Rich Client application. True: The menu is visible in the Rich Client Application False: The menu is not visible in the Rich Client Application

preference.name: CATIA_show_create_catpart_menu
preference.preference_description: Add the "Create CATPart dataset for selection" menu in the Teamcenter Rich Client application. True: The menu is visible in the Rich Client Application False: The menu is not visible in the Rich Client Application

preference.name: CATIA_show_create_catproduct_menu
preference.preference_description: Add the "Create CATProduct dataset for selection" menu in the Teamcenter Rich Client application. True: The menu is visible in the Rich Client Application False: The menu is not visible in the Rich Client Application

preference.name: CATIA_show_in_tc_rac_perspective
preference.preference_description: Defines the perspective the Show in Teamcenter command should be shown in the RAC Client.

preference.name: CATIA_show_in_tc_rac_view
preference.preference_description: Defines the view the Show in Teamcenter command should be shown in the RAC Client.

preference.name: CATIA_show_in_teamcenter_option
preference.preference_description: Determines which client the "Show in Teamcenter" command should open when the Teamcenter Integration for CATIA V5 Loader is connected to RACLess application and there is an AW client defined in the client_env file. Possible values: - AW : Open the selected item in Active Workspace. - LOADER: Open the selected item in TcIC Loader - DISPLAY : Displays a panel to select either the Active Workspace or Teamcenter Integration for CATIA Loader to open the selected item in.

preference.name: CATIA_silenced_import
preference.preference_description: Set this variable to true to write messages normally displayed during the Import process to the SilencedImport.Log file. Set the Silenced Import variable to false to display messages during the Import process.

preference.name: CATIA_stop_import_if_bad_status
preference.preference_description: Set the Stop Import if Bad Status variable to YES to stop the Import process when the status is false in the Import Spreadsheet. If one status in the spreadsheet is set to false, then: - NO = do nothing - MSG = prompt user to continue - YES = stop the Import process

preference.name: CATIA_stop_load_if_filename_conflict
preference.preference_description: When FileName conflicts are detected, set to true to stop the Load process; otherwise, set to false to continue the partial Load process, conflicting documents are excluded from the load process.

preference.name: CATIA_store_occ_uid_path_in_teamcenter
preference.preference_description: Use CATIA_store_occ_uid_path_in_teamcenter(=false) to improve performance on save with assemblies containing a lot of publications. However, this implies that data used to identify instances for the Read Linked Documents process are not saved: it could lead to misleading instances activation.

preference.name: CATIA_supplier_prefix
preference.preference_description: This property must not contain the same value of the CATIA_oem_prefix and it should not contain the prefix, EBS, to avoid data loss. Modify the Supplier Prefix variable to indicate the prefix of the CATIA properties used to save supplier property values in CATIA, i.e., prefix_originalPropertyName.

preference.name: CATIA_switch_in_visu_mode
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_switch_in_visu_mode variable to return to the original mode (Visualization or Design Mode) at the end of the Save process. If a part was in Visualization Mode at the beginning of the Save process, it is switched to Design Mode to retrieve information. Use this variable to indicate whether the part/assembly should remain in Design Mode or return to Visualization Mode at the end of the Save process. Parts in Visualization Mode or Design Mode at the beginning of the Save process are in Visualization Mode or Design Mode, respectively, at the end of the Save process when this variable is set to true. The assembly is always in Design Mode at the end of the Save process when this variable is set to false.

preference.name: CATIA_teamcenter_parameters_suffix
preference.preference_description: Suffix used for Teamcenter parameters created under the input folder or the output folder The default value, empty, is used when the preference or the preference value does not exist or is incorrect.

preference.name: CATIA_teamcenter_root_parameter_name
preference.preference_description: Name of the CATIA's root parameter set Apply Teamcenter Parameters when the preference or preference value does not exist or is incorrect.

preference.name: CATIA_thumbnails_extraction_filetypes
preference.preference_description: Extensions list compatible with thumbnails extraction

preference.name: CATIA_thumbnails_store_file_in_source_vol
preference.preference_description: Specifies that Thumbnails visualization data files for a source dataset will be stored in the same volume as the associated source dataset data files. The default value is true. If the value of this property is set to false, visualization data files will be stored in the TS Proxy User default volume. The TS Proxy User MUST be granted access to all volumes where source dataset data files are stored unless the value of this property is false. This property must be specified such that it applies to all Services.

preference.name: CATIA_to_mml_search_depth
preference.preference_description: Search depth of linked documents during drawing export process

preference.name: CATIA_tooltip_show_on_mouse_rollover
preference.preference_description: By default, the tooltip displays only when moving the mouse over the property name. If the preference is set to false, the tooltip displays when clicking on the the property name.

preference.name: CATIA_tooltip_show_on_mouse_rollover_delay
preference.preference_description: By default, the tooltip displays during a mouse rollover for more than 2000 ms.

preference.name: CATIA_tooltip_show_property_description
preference.preference_description: Show/Hide the property description in a tooltip.

preference.name: CATIA_ui_rendering_id
preference.preference_description: Defines the ID to use for the item of the XML that is used to organize properties in UI Panels. This preference is used for the Save manager, the Spreadsheet Editor and the Design Validation Report.

preference.name: CATIA_ui_title_format

preference.name: CATIA_update_drawing_before_saving
preference.preference_description: Set the CATIA_update_drawing_before_saving variable to true to update the drawing in CATIA during the Save process. Set this variable to false to prevent drawings from being updated in CATIA during the Save process.

preference.name: CATIA_update_import_spreadsheet
preference.preference_description: Preserve/Delete the current import spreadsheet when starting a create import spreadsheet process. Possible values: - true: Import spreadsheet is preserved. preference.name: CATIA_use_dataset_descriptor

preference.name: CATIA_volume_mass_ply_bl_prop

The default value will be used if the property specified does not exist, if it is not a string type or if it corresponds to the value of the preference CATIA_material_ply_bl_prop

preference.name: CATPART_item_type
preference.preference_description: Define a list of item types to use when saving a part, product, drawing, process, analysis or design table, by setting the following variables within Teamcenter Preferences. The default value of the item type is determined as follows: If the item type is defined in the CATPART_item_type, CATPRODUCT_item_type, etc. preference, then the item type used is the first listed in the preference list. The Save Manager only displays the available (defined) item types. If the item type preference is not defined, a list of all item types available in Teamcenter displays, and the default item type is defined by the CATIA_item_type Teamcenter Preference. If this type is not available then the first item type in Teamcenter list is the default item type. When Create New is applied from the Save Manager, the displayed item type is the existing item type. If this type is not available, then default values are used.

preference.name: ETS.PRIORITY.SIEMENS.CATIAV4TOJTDIRECT

preference.name: TCIC_co_warn_folder
preference.preference_description: Defines the subfolder used to paste the Item Revision (target) when a Check Out is performed on an Item Revision (source) from the Save Manager and the SpreadSheet Editor. The subfolder is from the HOME folder. The Subfolder will be created during the paste operation if it does not exist. The Subfolder will not be created if the preference is empty This preference is also used by the copy button of BMML

preference.name: TCIC_co_warn_link_types
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of link types between a source object and its target. Use the TCIC_co_warn_on_linked_doc preference to display a warning message during Check Out, if necessary, based on the links defined in this preference. Available Link Types: - To manage catia link type REF- REF: Content of CATIA_mml_link_type - To manage catia link type Ref-Inst: Content of CATIA_mmlassy_link_type - To manage catia link type DWG: Content of CATIA_drawing_link_type - To manage catia link type Process: Content of CATIA_manufacturing_link_type - To manage catia link type Analysis : Content of CATIA_analysis_link_type All others values are ignored

preference.name: TCIC_co_warn_on_linked_doc
preference.preference_description: Display a warning message when a Check Out is performed on a source object that is linked to targets in the Teamcenter database. The list of link types (link between a source object and its target) is defined in the TCIC_co_warn_link_types preference. By default, if the preference is not defined or if the preference is set to true, a warning message is displayed Possible values: - true: Display a warning message. - false: No warning.

preference.name: TCIC_ignore_DT_for_LFC
preference.preference_description: TCIC_ignore_DT_for_LFC preference can be used to disable export of Design Table files during Load For Compare process True: Design Table files are not exported to LFC directory during Load For Compare process (Even if CATIA_manage_designtables preference is set to true) False: Design Table files are exported to LFC directory during Load For Compare process (Unless CATIA_manage_designtables preference is set to false)
